# blue_sky CODEOWNERS — Zelis Engagement Attribution work
#
# ============================================================================
# Gate model — codeowner ≠ reviewer
# ============================================================================
# CODEOWNERS = approval-gate identities (humans: David + Atlas, plus the
# single-member reviewer Teams for path-specific co-ownership).
# The review team (Sage / Iris / Magnus = GitHub APPS, not users) is enforced
# via a Repository Ruleset's `required_reviewers` clause — not via this file.
# See docs/operations/pr-gate-protocol.md for the full pattern.
#
# Both gates must pass on every PR:
#   - 3 reviews from the review-team Apps (Rulesets required_reviewers, pinned
#     by single-member team-IDs — see protocol §6.4)
#   - 1 codeowner approval (this file + "Require review from Code Owners")
#
# ============================================================================
# Why CODEOWNERS uses team slugs for path-specific lines, not App slugs
# ============================================================================
# GitHub's CODEOWNERS syntax accepts users, teams, and email addresses ONLY.
# App slugs (e.g. `bluesky-sage[bot]`) are NOT valid CODEOWNERS entries:
#   https://docs.github.com/articles/about-code-owners
#
# Each reviewer App is therefore wrapped in a single-member org Team:
#   bluesky-sage[bot]   → sole member of @experance-dev/reviewer-sage
#   bluesky-iris[bot]   → sole member of @experance-dev/reviewer-iris
#   bluesky-magnus[bot] → sole member of @experance-dev/reviewer-magnus
#
# This file uses the team slugs for path-scoped co-ownership. When the App
# posts an approval review via installation token, the bot user is recognized
# as a member of the team, satisfying the CODEOWNERS rule for that path.
#
# ============================================================================
# Codeowner identities — humans
# ============================================================================
#   David Wood    — primary approver       → @david-wood
#   Atlas         — codeowner peer, preferred fallback when David is offline
#                                          → @atlas         [TODO: confirm handle]
#
# When David is around, his approval is preferred; Atlas's is the fallback.
# Every Atlas approval is logged in docs/operations/atlas-standin-approvals.log
# with full context — Atlas is a real codeowner, not a workaround.
#
# ============================================================================
# Path-scoped co-ownership — single-member Teams wrapping reviewer Apps
# ============================================================================
# These Teams must exist in `experance-dev` with exactly one member each
# (the corresponding App's bot user). See protocol §7 for provisioning.
#
#   Sage (security)    → @experance-dev/reviewer-sage    [TODO: org team]
#   Iris (PO)          → @experance-dev/reviewer-iris    [TODO: org team]
#   Magnus (standards) → @experance-dev/reviewer-magnus  [TODO: org team]
#
# Test canon stays on the existing human Pippa/Verity model until those
# personas migrate to Apps. Pippa + Verity have GH user accounts pending.
#
#   Pippa Codey    → @pippa-codey     [TODO: confirm handle]
